                     An interactive television broadcast

              Operations Security Forum ITV (Internet Content)
                             (Course #ISC-002D)
                         Tuesday, November 20, 2001
                    12 noon-2 PM EST (10 AM-12 noon MST)

    Because there are no breaks for lunch, consider bringing a sack lunch
                              to the classroom.

   Download Materials (will open in a separate window)
   Kinsey comment: Web Content Meeting -- review of guidance materials
   John Fredlund comments
   Web Information Review Process
   Kinsey comments: on list and guidance regarding web site content review
   Definition from Draft DOE Glossary
   Assessing Information on DOE Web Sites

   Description
   Internet Content: Discussion about which types of information are
   appropriate for Websites.

   Who will benefit
   DOE operations security practitioners

   Course Outcomes
   Upon successful completion of this forum, attendees will have an
   appreciation of the types of information that are appropriate for
   Websites.

                                Prerequisites
                                    None

                                  Materials
                                    None

                                    Cost
     This course is free of charge to DOE and DOE-contractor personnel.

   How to register
   Contact your local site training point of contact (POC) to enroll, or
   call registration at (505) 845-5170, ext. 332 to identify your point of
   contact. Please enroll by November 7, 2001.

   Downlink information
   If you are a site facilitator with technical questions about the
   broadcast, contact Lori Davis at (505) 845-5170, ext. 322
   (ldavis@nnsi.doe.gov).


